CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 3, 1962, pg. 14A, reads: "Terri, the guest star of the D.I. show, was adored by the huge audience.  Here she wears an orange outfit.  She modeled her own wardrobe for the D.I.'s MENDS benefit, 'Melody of Fashion', held at the Holiday House."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of model Terri Springer wearing an orange sleeveless dress, double strand beaded necklace, light colored gloves,and light colored tall hat with dark band, standing in front of musicians in Holiday House for the D. I. Club's "Melody in Fashion" benefit for MENDS
